## Serialize Fields Using PHP Code

You can use either the serialization feature in WP All Import to import the key and value pairs, or a [custom PHP function](https://www.wpallimport.com/documentation/inline-php/) to return the value in the proper format needed by your theme or plugin. As an example, here's a custom function that returns the same array as shown in the example above:

```
function my_serialize($url, $thumbnail) {
    $array_var = array(
        'url' => $url,
        'thumbnail' => $thumbnail
    );
    return serialize($array_var);
}
//Usage: [my_serialize({url[1]},{thumbnail[1]})]
```

